<ns10:section xmlns:ns10="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.ejb3.enterpriseBeans.sessionBeans.businessInterfaces.businessLogicComponents">
	<ns11:title xmlns:ns11="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Enterprise beans as business logic components</ns11:title>
	<ns12:para xmlns:ns12="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		The business interface represents the contract for enterprise beans. It
		decouples the client from any particular bean implementation and enables one
		to substitute one realization of a business contract with another,
		<ns13:abbrev xmlns:ns13="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns13:abbrev> it realizes pluggability.
	</ns12:para>
	<ns14:para xmlns:ns14="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
		The pre-conditions are specified by the exceptions thrown in the business
		interface, <ns15:abbrev xmlns:ns15="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns15:abbrev> for each pre-conditions there will be an exception. 
	</ns14:para>
</ns10:section>